text: one-north MRT Station (CC23) is an MRT Station in Singapore. It is a Station on the Circle MRT Line. The station was opened on 8 October 2011 and is the only one on the entire MRT whose name does not start with a capital letter. It is located opposite Dover and serves the Industrial estate and schools nearby. ==Naming== The name one-north was selected to reflect the geographical location of Singapore, at one degree north. ==References== Category:Mass Rapid Transit (Singapore) stations
